member.example:
This sample shows how to call SendEnumPropertyModelAsync with required request content.

var client = new EnumPropertiesBasicClient();

var data = new {
    Day = "Monday",
    FixedDay = "Monday",
    Language = "English",
    Title = "1",
};

Response response = await client.SendEnumPropertyModelAsync(RequestContent.Create(data));
Console.WriteLine(response.Status);

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the request payload.
Request Body:
Schema for InputModel: { Day: "Monday" | "Tuesday" | "Wednesday" | "Thursday" | "Friday" | "Saturday" | "Sunday", # Required. Required standard enum value. FixedDay: "Monday" | "Tuesday" | "Wednesday" | "Thursday" | "Friday" | "Saturday" | "Sunday", # Required. Required fixed enum value. Language: "English" | "Spanish" | "Mandarin" | "Undocumented", # Required. Title: "1" | "2" | "3", # Required. }

